BOLA BAMIGBOLA A non-governmental organisation, Sustainable Impacts Aid, has donated empowerment tools to selected artisans, business grants to small scale business owners and mobility aids to people with special needs in Osun State. Speaking at the presentation of the items, the group said the initiative was meant to lessen the effects of the coronavirus pandemic on the beneficiaries and alleviate poverty among the populace. The beneficiaries, who were selected through a transparent selection process were presented grinding and sewing machines, hair dryers, vulcanising machines, mobility aids as well as business grants. Presenting the items to the beneficiaries, the Executive Secretary, Sustainable Impacts Aid, Oladeji Usman, said the initiative was implemented under the ‘Emergency Response Intervention Project,’ of the group, urging the beneficiares not to sell the empowerment tools but use them to improve their businesses. In her remarks, Osun State Commissioner for Work Affairs, Bukola Olaboopo, represented by Olutoyin Oyetola, said such assistance to the needy in the society would improve the economy of the state and assist in reducing poverty among the populace. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com   